 procedures, like ordinary procedures, can be manipulated as first-class objects and combined using functional composition. But unlike ordinary procedures, translucent procedures have structure that can be examined in well-specified non- destructive ways, without invoking the procedure.</p><p><u>Downloads:</u></p><ul><li><a href="http://repository.readscheme.org/ftp/papers/ai-lab-pubs/AITR-1427.ps.gz">ps</a></li><li><a href="http://repository.readscheme.org/ftp/papers/ai-lab-pubs/AITR-1427.pdf">pdf</a></li></ul><p><u>Bibtex citation:</u></p><pre>@techreport{
